  { Partition type UUID #fs-partition-type-uuid

    The partition type UUID (`PARTTYPE`, *not* `PARTUUID` in `lsblk`) is stored in the → hardware/harddisk/partition/table/GPT[GPT partition table] entry for that partition.

    Some important partition types in my little world are:
    table { ll

     `0fc63daf-8483-4772-8e79-3d69d8477de4` ☰ Linux filesystem data
     `c12a7328-f81f-11d2-ba4b-00a0c93ec93b` ☰ → hardware/UEFI/ESP[EFI System Partition]
     `de94bba4-06d1-4d40-a16a-bfd50179d6ac` ☰ Windows Recovery Environment
     `e3c9e316-0b5c-4db8-817d-f92df00215ae` ☰ Microsoft Reserved Partition (MSR)
     `ebd0a0a2-b9e5-4433-87c0-68b6b72699c7` ☰ Basic data partition (This seems to be a Microsoft thingy, reported as «Microsoft reserved» with `fdisk -l`)

    table }

    See also  → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GUID_Partition_Table#Partition_type_GUIDs[Wikipedia] (table must be opened).

